sentences: Bernd Begemann (born 1 November 1962 in Braunschweig as Kay Stephan Rönnau) is a contemporary German alt/pop singer-songwriter, actor, producer and filmmusic-composer linked to the Hamburger Schule.
In 1963, he was adopted by Bernhard Begemann at the age of six months, who gave him his new name.

He was very successful as sportsman as a teen and young adult and won a lot of competitions, because he was extremely talented as very fast runner but in the end of the 1970s, in his hometown of Bad Salzuflen (Germany) he became a punk and he founded in 1979 a punk rock band with the "real rebel name", "Vatikan".
1988 was the year that it finally happened: Die Antwort released its first CD.

Was macht Miss Juni im Dezember (1992)
From the middle to the end of the 1980s he was part of the Pop-music label "Fast Weltweit" (almost worldwide).
In 1963, he was adopted by Bernhard Begemann at the age of six months, who gave him his new name.

He was very successful as sportsman as a teen and young adult and won a lot of competitions, because he was extremely talented as very fast runner but in the end of the 1970s, in his hometown of Bad Salzuflen (Germany) he became a punk and he founded in 1979 a punk rock band with the "real rebel name", "Vatikan".

They released singles and cassette tape samplers, such as Jochen Distelmeyer's (later in the band Blumfeld) "Bienenjäger" with Thomas Wenzel (now in Die Goldenen Zitronen and Die Sterne) and the very first Die Sterne single.
1988 was the year that it finally happened: Die Antwort released its first CD.
Bernd Begemann celebrates 60 years anniversary of the Beatles in Hamburg
